\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b\f0\fs36\lang9                HIGH AVAILABILITY IN CLOUD COMPUTING.\par
\b0\fs28\par
"It refers to the design and implementation of systems and architectures that ensure a high level of operational continuity and reliability. "\par
The idea is to make your products, services, and tools available to your customers and employees at any time from anywhere using any device with an internet connection.\par
There are key elements for achieving high availability in cloud compution:\par
\b 1.Redundancy:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0  Multi - Region Deployments: A multi-region application is        deployed across multiple cloud availability zones or regions. \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab} Multi-Availability Zone (AZ) Deployments:   Cloud providers typically offer multiple availability zones within a region.Deploying resources across these zones helps ensure availability in the event of failures.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 2.Load Balancing:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0  Distributes traffic and workloads to ensure that no single server or machine is under-loaded, overloaded, or idle. \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab} Load balancers can automatically route traffic to healthy instances, improving performance and availability.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 3.Auto-scaling:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Dynamically adjust the number of compute resources based on demand.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Autoscaling is a cloud computing feature that enables organizations to scale cloud services such as server capacities or virtual machines up or down automatically, based on defined situations such as traffic ir utilization levels.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 4.Fault Tolerance:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Design applications and infrastructure to withstand failures without impacting overall system availability.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Use redundant components and implement error-handling mechanisms.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 5.Data Backup and Replication:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Regularly backup data and store copies in different locations. \par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Implement data replication across multiple data centers or regions to ensure data availability even in the event of a failure.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 6. Monitoring and Alerts:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0  Set up monitoring tools to continuously track the health and performance of your infrastructure.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Implement alerting mechanisms to notify administrators of potential issues or deviations from normal behavior.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 7.Automated Recovery:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Implement automated recovery procedures to quickly respond to failures.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Automation tools can help in automatically restoring services, replacing failed instances, and recovering from disruptions.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 8.Disaster Recovery (DR) Planning:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Develop a comprehensive disaster recovery plan that outlines procedures for handling major outages.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Regularly test the disaster recovery plan to ensure its effectiveness.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 9.Regular Maintenance:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Perform routine maintenance tasks, such as software updates and security patches, without causing downtime.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Use rolling updates and canary releases to minimize the impact of updates.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 10.Security Best Practices:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Implement security measures to protect against unauthorized access and data breaches.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Regularly audit and update security policies to address emerging threats.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1                             \par
\b\fs36                        Auto Scalling in Cloud Computing.\par
\b0\fs28 "Auto-scaling in cloud computing is a feature that enables the automatic adjustment of computing resources based on changes in demand for an application or service. The goal of auto-scaling is to ensure optimal performance and cost efficiency by dynamically adding or removing resources as needed, without manual intervention. "Here's how auto-scaling typically works:\par
\par
\b 1.Monitoring Metrics:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Auto-scaling relies on monitoring metrics to assess the health and performance of the system. Common metrics include CPU utilization, network traffic, memory usage, and application-specific metrics.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 2.Scaling Policies:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0  Organizations define scaling policies that specify the conditions under which scaling actions should be triggered. These policies are based on thresholds set for the monitored metrics.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}For example, a scaling policy might specify that if CPU utilization exceeds a certain threshold for a specified period, additional instances should be added.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 3.Scaloing Actions:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 When the defined conditions are met, scaling actions are triggered. These actions can be either scaling out (adding more resources) or scaling in (removing resources).\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Scaling actions can apply to various types of resources, such as virtual machines, containers, or serverless functions, depending on the cloud service used.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 4.Integration with Load Balancers:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 In many auto-scaling scenarios, resources are added or removed in conjunction with a load balancer. This ensures that incoming traffic is evenly distributed among the available instances.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Load balancers play a crucial role in maintaining high availability and distributing workloads effectively.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 5.Dynamic Resource Provisioning:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Auto-scaling dynamically provisions resources, such as virtual machines or containers, to meet the changing demands of the application.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Cloud providers offer services and APIs that facilitate the automatic creation and deletion of instances based on scaling policies.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 6.Cooldown Periods:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 To prevent rapid and unnecessary scaling actions in response to short-lived spikes in demand, auto-scaling configurations often include cooldown periods. During these periods, further scaling actions are temporarily disabled.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 7.Scheduled Scaling:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Some applications may experience predictable changes in demand based on time of day, day of the week, or other patterns. Auto-scaling can be configured to handle scheduled scaling actions, adjusting resources according to predefined schedules.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 8.Integration with Orchestration Tools:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Auto-scaling is often integrated with orchestration tools or services that manage the deployment and lifecycle of applications. This can include services like Kubernetes for containerized applications or AWS Elastic Beanstalk for simplified deployment.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b                                       \fs36 Resilience in Cloud Computing.\par
\b0\fs28 "Resilience in cloud computing refers to the ability of a system or application to withstand and recover from failures, disruptions, or unexpected events while maintaining acceptable levels of service and performance. Building resilient systems in the cloud is crucial for ensuring continuous availability, minimizing downtime, and providing a reliable user experience. Here are key principles and practices to enhance resilience in cloud computing."\par
\b 1.Redundancy:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Distribute critical components and data across multiple availability zones (AZs) or regions to reduce the impact of failures in a single location.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Implement redundant infrastructure, such as load balancers and replicated databases, to ensure that a failure in one component does not lead to a system-wide outage.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 2.Automated Monitoring:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0  Implement comprehensive monitoring of the entire cloud infrastructure, including application performance, resource utilization, and security.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Use automated alerting to quickly detect and respond to issues, allowing for proactive resolution before they impact users.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 3.Auto-Scaling:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Utilize auto-scaling features to dynamically adjust resources based on demand. This helps maintain optimal performance during traffic spikes and reduces costs during periods of low demand.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Auto-scaling can also enhance resilience by replacing failed instances automatically and redistributing traffic.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 4.Load Balancing:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Implement load balancers to distribute incoming traffic across multiple servers or instances. This ensures that no single component becomes a bottleneck and helps prevent service degradation.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Load balancers contribute to high availability and fault tolerance by routing traffic to healthy instances.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 5.Disaster Recovery Planning:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Develop and regularly test a comprehensive disaster recovery (DR) plan that includes procedures for data backup, restoration, and failover.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Consider cross-region or multi-cloud disaster recovery strategies to protect against large-scale outages.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 6.Immutable Infrastructure:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Implement an immutable infrastructure approach, where infrastructure components are treated as disposable and are replaced rather than patched or modified.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Immutable infrastructure can simplify rollbacks and reduce the risk of configuration-related issues.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 7.Data Backups and Replication:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Regularly back up critical data and ensure that backups are stored in geographically diverse locations.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Implement data replication to maintain copies of data in different regions, providing redundancy and protection against data loss.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 8.Chaos Engineering:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Conduct controlled experiments, known as chaos engineering, to simulate failures and assess how well the system responds.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Chaos engineering helps identify weaknesses in the system and allows for proactive improvements to enhance resilience.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 9.Security Measures:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Integrate robust security measures to protect against cyber threats and unauthorized access.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Regularly update and patch software to address vulnerabilities and reduce the risk of security breaches.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b 10.Compliance and Standards:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Adhering to industry standards and compliance requirements to ensure that the cloud infrastructure meets regulatory expectations, which often include considerations for data resilience and availability.\par

